@node FEATURES "Overview of all new Features included in FileID V2.00"

@{u}Short Overview of all new Features@{uu}

- Users are able to choose, if FileID should 'drop' the user after he has
  completed his upload, so he don't have to wait before all files are 
  checked.

- FileID V2.00 is able to stay resident in memory (only in the Registered 
  Version!)

- The Size of the Descriptions is now selectable via @{"ToolTypes" LINK TOOLTYPES}

- FileID now uses a Brainfile which allows to remember some strange Descr.
  containing lame adverts or other shit. With this option, FileID is able
  to cut such shit out of the Descriptions.

- As second feature, FileID is able to cut ANSI- and CTRL-Codes out of the
  description and replace them with Spaces, so your File-Listing won't be
  destroyed with such nasty chars.

- FileID now uses the FileID.library V2++ written by Bloodrock/SDC to 
  determine the Filetyp, and therefor it's now impossible to confuse FileID
  with Files which have not the right extension (i.e. DMS-Archive with .LHA)

- Is able to manage two different Sent-By Lines, maybe different ones for 
  each conference, if the desired ToolType is set.

- New packers could be added simply by specifying the new ToolTypes for
  the new packer.

- From now on, FileID is able to check the FileName for a Group-Synonym,
  i.e. the Filename is 'TRSI_SD1.LHA' or 'TRSI-SD1.LHA', and no File_ID.DIZ
  is included in the archive, FileID looks in a special Directory for the
  TRSI-Logos and if found, shows them to the user to allow him to choose
  a group-logo for the uploaded file.
  
- FileID V2.00 is able to switch off his Outputs, so you got a faster 
  checking.

- The Autosent Program is now integrated in FileID, so you have only one
  Program for both functions.

...if you want to install it now (highly recommended ! :), take a look to
the chapter @{"Installation" LINK INSTALLATION} before using FileID !
@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "Installation & Requirements needed for FileID"

@{u}Requirements@{uu}

- A500-A4000T with Kickstart V2.++ and a full installed Amiex V3/4++

@{u}NOTE:@{uu} If you are upgrading from a previous version of FileID V2.00, please
      make sure that you delete everything created by the old FileID, 
      including the Sent.Dats !!!! If you don't do this, you may become
      Problems using FileID!!!

@{u}The Installation of FileID V2.00 to your BBS@{uu}

@{b}1.@{ub} Copy the hole FileID/ drawer to your DOORS: drawer. This drawer also
   include the Logos drawer for the File-Description-Grouplogos. Make sure
   that you copy FileID only in this Drawer, otherwise FileID V2.00 won't
   work !!!!!

@{b}2.@{ub} Copy the Icons Stupid.info, Sent.info and U.info to your BBSCMD-drawer.

The icons have the following functions:

@{u}Stupid.info@{uu}: This is the 'Brain-File' of FileID. Enter Stupid in the Amiex,
             and define the Lines FileID should strip out of descriptions,
             i.e.: you define as Line : Uploaded
             and FileID founds : Uploaded by Godfather of Soul, than this
             Line will be stripped out of the Description.

@{u}Sent.info@{uu}  : With this command the users could define their own Sentby-Lines.
             Two different methods of using the Sentby-Line are included and
             switchable via ToolTypes.
             After entering your private sentbyline, FileID gives you the
             ability to center your Sentby-Line.

@{u}U.info@{uu}     : This Command works similar to the old method of starting FileID
             before Uploading. In previous Versions, you have to start
             FileID with a MCI-Command in your UPLOADMSG.TXT to ask the user
             if he wants to use FileID for the descriptions. Now, if a user
             enters U, he will be asked if he wants to use FileID. No need
             of MCI-Commands anymore. Of course you don't have to use this
             option, it's just another Feature...:)

@{b}3.@{ub} Now copy the Icon Examine.info to your SYSCMD-Drawer. If you already have
   an Examine-Tool installed, simply count them up in logical order, meaning
   Examine.info (Dupecheck), Examine1.info (FileID) etc.

   @{u}NOTE:@{uu} This Function is only available from Amiex V4.++ !!!!

   If you using an older Version of amiex which don't allow to have more 
   than one Examine.Info, kick it out and use FileID instead!

That's all for installation....for an complete overview of all ToolType-
Informations take a look to the Chapter @{"ToolTypes" LINK TOOLTYPES}.
@endnode

@node TOOLTYPES "All ToolType-Definitions for FileID V2.00"

@{u}All Tooltypes used by FileID V2.00@{uu}

NODE_SENT             - With this Tooltype you define a Sentby-Line which
                        includes the Nodenummer and the Time the file was 
                        uploaded. Between the Nodenr and the Time the User
                        could insert his own handle. The Sentby-Line has the
                        following format:

                           [NODE 11] xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx [20:21:23]

                        This Sentby-Line is colored until you set the Tool-
                        type NO_ANSI.

AUTOSENT              - This is the standard Sentby-Line. Here you could all
                        44 chars for your private Sentby. If a user has no
                        defined Sentby-Line, a default Line will be used, 
                        which is also colored. The Color could be disabled
                        by setting the ToolType NO_ANSI.

SENT_PER_CONF         - If this ToolType is set, all users could have 
                        different Sentby-Lines for each conference.

DEFAULT_SENT=<string> - Here you could define an alternate Default-Sentby-
                        Line which will used by Users, which hasn't define
                        their private Sentbyline. Make sure that you only
                        enter max. 14 Chars for this Tooltype, all chars
                        over 14 will be cutted ! 

NO_ANSI               - Set this ToolType if you want no Colors used.

NO_OUTPUT             - This Option disables the normal Output of FileID.
                        If set, the user only see that FileID is searching
                        for an description.

SHOW_LOGOS            - When set, this Option let FileID first check out the
                        Filename for a known Prefix, and if found, displays
                        the related Group-Logo(s), i.e. if the filename is
                        TRSI-BK.LHA, FileID search for TRSI -Logos in
                        DOORS:FILEID/LOGOS/ ...

DESCRIPTION_ONLY      - If a user chooses Logoff after Upload, and the ul'ed
                        Files have no FileDescriptions, this Files will be
                        normally moved to FileListing with a Filedescription
                        called: UPLOAD WITHOUT FILEID

                        But if you want to have only files online, which
                        have a FileDescription, set this ToolType and if a
                        file without Filedescription will be uploaded, this
                        File will be moved to the Partupload-Directory and
                        displayed to the user at his next Login !

DEF_TAGLINE=<string>  - if you are bothered of my poor english :), here you
                        could enter a new Top text, which will be displayed
                        before showing the File-Description..if you don't
                        specify this ToolType, the default String will be 
                        displayed (Don't write your Tagline here....)

TIME_TO_ASK_ID=<x>    - This Tooltype specifies the Time FileID will wait
                        before automatically using the found description.
                        This value is in seconds. If you don't specify this
                        option, FileID won't ask the user and use the 
                        description in every case.
                        NOTE: This Tooltype overrides the NO_OUTPUT Option,
                        meaning if you have this Tooltype set, FileID WILL
                        display his full output!!! 

TIME_TO_ASK_SENT=<x>  - This Tooltype specifies the Time FileID will wait
                        before automatically using the SentBy-Line. This
                        value is in seconds. If you don't specify this 
                        option, FileID don't ask for using the Sentby-Line.
                        If you specify the ToolType 'NODESENT', this option
                        takes no effect !
                        If you have NO_OUTPUT specified and this Tooltype
                        set, too, the NO_OUTPUT-Option will be disabled !


TXT_TYPE=TXT/DOC...   - Here you could define different Textfile-Extensions.
                        In the actual Version, FileID.Library is unable to
                        identify different Text-formats like ANSI,ASCII etc.
                        To let FileID work correct with those files, specify
                        here the extensions of the Textfiles (.ans, .nfo),
                        and FileID takes the settings from the ToolTypes 
                        after identifying the File as Text-File.


     @{"For the packer-related Tooltypes press Play on tape please..:)" LINK TOOLTYPES2}
@endnode

@node TOOLTYPES2 "All packer-related ToolTypes"

@{u}ToolTypes for the Packer-Support@{uu}

To support the different Packer-/fileformats, there exists some Tooltypes,
which define how FileID should handle those files...the tooltypes have the
following Format:

LHA_ADD=C:LHA a %P %WFILE_ID.DIZ  <-> For adding an File_ID.DIZ

LHA_EX=C:LHA e %P FILE_ID.DIZ %W  <-> For extracting FILE_ID.DIZ

The '%' commands have the following Meaning:

%F = The FileName
%P = Path for the Playpen and Filename
%W = Path for the Workdir

For every (currently) supported Packer, FileID looks for the following
ToolTypes:

                  @{u}PACKER@{uu}                     @{u}TOOLTYPES@{uu}

                   DMS                    DMS_ADD / DMS_EX
                   ARJ                    ARJ_ADD / ARJ_EX
                 UNKNOWNEXE               EXE_ADD / EXE_EX
                  EXELINK                 EXE_ADD / EXE_EX
                   ZOO                    ZOO_ADD / ZOO_EX
                   ZIP                    ZIP_ADD / ZIP_EX
                   ZOOM                  ZOOM_ADD / ZOOM_EX
                   LHWARP              LHWARP_ADD / LHWARP_EX
                 GIFPICTURE               GIF_ADD / GIF_EX
                   LHASFX                 LHA_ADD / LHA_EX
                   LHA                    LHA_ADD / LHA_EX
                   WARP                  WARP_ADD / WARP_EX
                   ARC                    ARC_ADD / ARC_EX
                  SHRINK                  SHR_ADD / SHR_EX
                   TXT                    TXT_ADD / TXT_EX

This Packertypes will be recognized automatically by FileID. If maybe in the
Future comes new Packers which couldn't be handled by FileID, you always 
have the possibility to add those filetypes by using the Tooltypes. The only
changing is that you have to add the word 'EXTERN_' before the File-
extension, i.e.

The filename is "FIleID.ojx", than you have to enter the following tooltypes
to allow FileID to handle this filetype correct:

                  EXTERN_OJX_EX=C:OJX e %P FILE_ID.DIZ %W
                 EXTERN_OJX_ADD=C:OJX a %P FILE_ID.DIZ %W

Hope you understand how to install new packers....:)
@endnode

